snippet: It wasn’t the greatest year for quarterback Jameis Winston, even though he led Florida State to an undefeated record and a coveted spot in the College Football Playoff.
abstract: Marc Tracy On College Football column examines conspicuous absence of Florida State quarterback Jameis Winston among list of finalists for the Heisman Trophy; speculates that Winston's involvement in off-the-field scandals has run afoul of word 'integrity' in award's mission statement, blocking him from a second consecutive victory, but notes that there is no official reason that he should have been left out of consideration.
lead_paragraph: It wasn’t the greatest year for quarterback Jameis Winston, even though he led Florida State to an undefeated record and a coveted spot in the College Football Playoff.

headline.main: On the Narrow Path to Second Heisman, Jameis Winston Stumbled
headline.print_headline: On the Narrow Path to a 2nd Heisman, Winston Stumbled
